abstract: >-
  Lemmata is a browser-based, multilingual LDA topic modeling platform
  designed for humanities researchers with no programming expertise.
  It supports Italian, English, German, French, and Spanish through
  spaCy NLP pipelines, and produces fully deterministic, reproducible
  results (random_state=42, batch learning). The platform was developed
  entirely through vibe coding — LLM-assisted software development
  using natural language prompts — and serves as both a practical
  research tool and a methodological case study for AI-assisted
  Digital Humanities workflows.
